question: Question_01_(e)
statement:
For each of the following multiple-choice questions, there is one
correct answer. Circle the corresponding (roman) numeral.

$\displaystyle 1 -2x^{2}$ is the second order Taylor polynomial (around
$x=0$) for which one of the following functions?

i. $\displaystyle 1 -\sin(4x)$

ii. $\displaystyle e^{-x^{2}}$

iii. $\displaystyle \cos(2x)$

iv. $\displaystyle e^{-4x}$

v. $\displaystyle \cos(x)$
